abstract: Al Franken, the humorist and founder of Air America, announced his candidacy for Senate in Minnesota.

lead_paragraph: Suddenly, the idea of Jon Stewart and Stephen Colbert on a presidential ticket doesn’t seem so far-fetched. Not now that Al Franken, the comedian, ex-Air America host (as of today) and author (“Rush Limbaugh is a Big, Fat Idiot”) is asking “Why Not Me?” for real.
